Attā hi [attāpi (?)] attano natthi, kuto puttā kuto dhanaṃ.', '"Sons have I, wealth have I",
thus the fool is fretful.
He himself is not his own,
how then are sons, how wealth?', 'Phẩm Ngu', 'Balavagga', 'Fools');
